section.def:
contravention
                (違反、違例事項)
            means a contravention of any of the provisions of section 4;

driver
                (司機), in relation to a motor vehicle, means any
            person who is in charge of or assisting in the control of it;

proceedings
                (法律程序) means proceedings before a magistrate
            under section 11(1) or (2);

paragraph.content:
the person in whose name a motor vehicle is registered in accordance with
                    the Road Traffic Ordinance (Cap. 374);
                    and

section.def:
sign
                (標誌) has the same meaning as in the Housing
            (Traffic) By-laws (Cap. 283 sub. leg. A);

paragraph.content:
if that person wishes to dispute liability for the contravention, order
                    that the matter be determined in accordance with section 11(1);
                    or

the sum adjudged to be paid, or where the application for an order under
                    this section is in respect of more than one sum adjudged to be paid, the total
                    of such sums;
